  <li><strong>Master the Merlot Temperature Gradient</strong> - Serve Merlot at 60-65°F (15-18°C), but understand that different styles require slight adjustments. Right Bank Bordeaux Merlot-based blends (like Pomerol) benefit from the cooler end at 60°F to preserve their silky tannin structure, while fuller-bodied Napa Valley Merlots can handle 65°F to showcase their ripe fruit concentration. Let the wine warm 2-3 degrees in the glass to unlock secondary aromatics.</li>

