  <li><strong>Decant Based on Vintage and Region, Not Age Alone</strong> - Young, tannic Merlots from Bordeaux's Right Bank (under 10 years) benefit from 2-3 hours of decanting to soften their structure. However, mature Merlots (15+ years) from any region should only be decanted 30 minutes before serving, as extended air exposure can strip away their delicate tertiary aromatics of leather, truffle, and dried herbs.</li>

